article.headline: Northwestern St. 77, East Texas Bapt 74
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Tyronn Mitchell recorded his fourth steal as Cedric Isom went up for a potential game-tying 3-point shot just before the final buzzer and Northwestern State escaped with a 77-74 win over Division III East Texas Baptist Friday. Clifton Lee scored 18 points for the Demons (1-0), Byron Allen added 15 points Luke Rogers had 14 and Jermaine Spencer had 11. Allen's three-point play with 2:15 to go produced the game's fifth tie at 73-73 and Lee's putback with 1:37 to go put Northwestern State ahead for good. The Tigers led 40-33 at the half, and were up 62-51 in the second before Northwestern ran off 10 unanswered points, with Allen dunking with 4:27 left to give the Demons their first lead since late in the first half. Allen scored 11 of his points in the final 12 minutes, including seven in the final four minutes. Cedric Isom led the Tigers (0-1) with 28 points and seven assists. Brannon Ott added 20 points and Chris Isom scored 17 points.
